## вҡ пёҸ COMMON MISTAKES TO AVOID

### **вқҢ Mistake 1: Using std::cout**
```cpp
// Wrong
std::cout << "Error: " << error << std::endl;

// Right
Logger::error("Error: {}", error);
```

### **вқҢ Mistake 2: Using exceptions**
```cpp
// Wrong
throw std::runtime_error("Failed");

// Right
return std::unexpected(Error::Failed);
```

### **вқҢ Mistake 3: Raw pointers**
```cpp
// Wrong
Logger* logger = new Logger();
delete logger;

// Right
auto logger = std::make_unique<Logger>();
```

### **вқҢ Mistake 4: Mixing Qt/std**
```cpp
// Wrong
std::vector<QString> mixed;

// Right
std::vector<std::string> coreData;
QString uiString = QString::fromStdString(coreData[0]);
```

### **вқҢ Mistake 5: Sync I/O**
```cpp
// Wrong
QProcess process;
process.start("command");
process.waitForFinished();  // Blocks UI!

// Right
connect(&process, &QProcess::finished, this, &MyClass::onFinished);
process.start("command");
```

